A suspected cattle rustler on Monday committed suicide in a toilet at Homa Bay police cells using his trousers.Otieno Okoth was arrested at Rodi Kopany market in Homa Bay town onFriday and was to be charged in the morning with theft. Okoth, 25, told his cellmates that he only needed to answer nature's call but ended up killing himself at about 1am, said Homa Bay county police commander John Omusanga. Investigations are underway but our preliminary report reveals he committed suicide because his family members were not happy with his habit of cattle rustling," said Omusanga.He added that Okoth's parents were unwilling to help him with the case but urged young people to shun criminal activities.The man's body was taken to the Homa Bay County Referral Hospital mortuary.